content.text: PURCHASE AND SALE
content.caption: PURCHASE AND SALE

content.text: Purchase and Sale.  Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, Seller hereby agrees to sell and convey to Purchaser, free and clear of all liens, security interests, encumbrances, easements and restrictions (“Encumbrances”) other than Permitted Encumbrances (as defined below), and Purchaser hereby agrees to purchase from Seller, all of the following described property (herein collectively called the “Property”):
content.caption: Purchase and Sale.

content.text: Land.  That certain tract of land located at 5890 S 129th Street, Seattle, Washington , containing approximately [_____] acres of land, and being more particularly described on Exhibit A attached hereto and made a part hereof (herein, the “Land”).
content.caption: Land.

content.text: Easements.  All easements, licenses and other non-possessory interests, if any, benefiting the Land or the Improvements (as defined in Section 1.1(d) of this Agreement).
content.caption: Easements.

content.text: Rights and Appurtenances.  All rights and appurtenances pertaining to the Land, including, without limitation, any right, title and interest of Seller in and to adjacent streets, alleys or rights-of-way, any and all mineral and water rights and other appurtenances used or connected with the beneficial use or enjoyment of the Land and/or the Improvements.
content.caption: Rights and Appurtenances.

content.text: Improvements.  All improvements, associated parking and landscaped areas and related amenities in and on the Land, comprising 72,625 net rentable square feet of storage space and 822 rental storage units, and being commonly known as “StorQuest – Seattle/129th” (herein, the “Improvements”).
content.caption: Improvements.

content.text: Leases.  Seller’s interest under (i) all written leases, licenses, occupancy agreements and rental agreements for rental units in the Property (collectively, the “Leases”), including all tenant leasing files, together with all refundable tenant security deposits (if any) and prepaid rentals and whatever rights of any kind or nature related thereto paid or made by tenants occupying the Property and not applied by Seller or otherwise pursuant to the applicable Leases, together with interest owing thereon pursuant to the applicable Lease, if any, held or required to be held by Seller pursuant to the Leases on the Closing Date (as defined below) (collectively, “Security Deposits”), (ii) all cellular tower leases, licenses, or other agreements relating to the use of the Property for cellular tower purposes, together with any and all security deposits relating thereto and/or prepaid inducement fees and/or incentive payments paid by such occupants, if any, prorated as of the Closing Date pursuant to Section 6.4 below, as more particularly described on Schedule B attached hereto and incorporated herein (the “Tower Leases”), and (iii) all billboard leases,  licenses, or other agreements relating to the use of the Property for billboard purposes, together with any and all security deposits relating thereto and/or prepaid inducement fees and/or incentive payments paid by such occupants, if any, prorated as of the Closing Date pursuant to Section 6.4 below, as more particularly described on Schedule C attached hereto and incorporated herein (the “Billboard Leases”).
content.caption: Leases.

content.text: Tangible Personal Property. All appliances, fixtures, apparatus, equipment, machinery, furniture, carpet, drapes and other items of personal property now or hereafter owned by Seller and located on or about the Land and the Improvements and used in the ownership and operation of the Land and Improvements (collectively, the “Tangible Personal Property”), including, without limitation, those items of personal property set forth on Exhibit E attached hereto, and further including all on-site moving trucks, if any, listed on Exhibit E attached hereto (herein collectively, the “Motor Vehicles”).
content.caption: Tangible Personal Property.

content.text: Contracts.  Seller’s interest (to the extent the same is assignable) under the Contracts (as defined below), other than the Rejected Contracts (as defined below).
content.caption: Contracts.

content.text: Permits and Licenses.  Any permit, entitlement, governmental approval, certificate of occupancy, license or other form of authorization or approval issued by a government agency or authority and legally required for the construction, ownership, operation and use of the Property to the extent transferable with the sale of the Property.
content.caption: Permits and Licenses.

content.text: Plans and Surveys.  All plans, surveys, specifications, drawings, architectural and engineering drawings, and other rights relating to the construction of the Property, to the extent in Seller’s possession or control.
content.caption: Plans and Surveys.

content.text: Warranties and Guaranties. Any written warranty, guaranty, or other obligation from any contractor, manufacturer or vendor to any improvements, furnishings, fixture or equipment located at the Property, to the extent assignable in connection with the sale of the Property.
content.caption: Warranties and Guaranties.

content.text: Intangible Property.  All intangible property owned by Seller and pertaining to the Land, the Improvements, or the Tangible Personal Property, including, without limitation, (i) all “yellow page” advertisements, (ii) all transferable utility contracts, (iii) all transferable telephone exchange numbers, including the telephone numbers (206) 745-3868, (iv) the goodwill, reputation and prestige associated with the Property and the business located thereon (“Goodwill”), and (v) the digital assets and items listed on Exhibit I attached hereto (collectively, the “Intangible Property”).
content.caption: Intangible Property.

content.text: Excluded Items.  Notwithstanding the foregoing, the “Property” shall not include the following (collectively, “Excluded Items”):  (a) materials relating to the marketing efforts for the sale of the Property, including communications and agreements with other potential purchasers; (b) projections and other internal memoranda or materials; (c) communications between Seller (or its advisors or affiliates) and the property manager and/or leasing broker for the Property; (d) bank accounts, appraisals, budgets, strategic plans for the Property, internal analyses (including analyses with respect to its leasing of space in the Property), computer software, and submissions relating to the obtaining of internal authorizations, and engineering and environmental reports received by Seller or its affiliates or advisors; (e) attorney and accountant work product, and all other materials subject to any legal privilege in favor of Seller; (f) organizational documents of the Seller and Seller’s direct and indirect owners, and their respective agents, officers, directors, trustees, advisors, managers, members, agents, owners, employees and counsel (“Seller Parties”) and any agreements and communications between Seller and any affiliate or advisor of Seller; (g) the personal property located in the on-site management office or elsewhere used by the current property manager for the Property and not owned by Seller; and (h) the names “ASB”, “WWG”, “William Warren Group”, “StorQuest” or any variations or derivations thereof, whether alone or in combination with one or more other words.  In addition, the term “Property” shall not include any current or contingent debts, liabilities or obligations pertaining to the Property, or otherwise pertaining to Seller.  Seller specifically acknowledges that, except as specifically set forth in this Agreement or any document executed by Purchaser and delivered to Seller pursuant to this Agreement, Purchaser does not assume any liability or obligation whatsoever which presently exists and which may arise in connection with the transfer of the Property, including but not limited to the payment of any sums owing to employees, creditors or mechanics lien claimants with respect to the Property, the obligation to perform under any contract, or any responsibility for the payment of the accounts payable.
content.caption: Excluded Items.

content.text: PURCHASE PRICE; EARNEST MONEY
content.caption: PURCHASE PRICE; EARNEST MONEY

content.text: Purchase Price.  The purchase price (the “Purchase Price”) for the Property shall be the sum of Sixteen Million Two Hundred Fifty Thousand and 00/100 Dollars ($16,250,000.00), subject to prorations and adjustments as set forth in this Agreement, and shall be paid by Purchaser to Seller at the Closing by wire transfer of immediately available funds to the Escrow Agent (as defined below) on the Closing Date in accordance with wire transfer instructions to be provided by the Escrow Agent.  The parties hereto agree that Purchaser, at its sole discretion, may allocate up to twenty-five percent (25%) of the Purchase Price to Goodwill.
content.caption: Purchase Price.

content.text: Earnest Money.
content.caption: Earnest Money.

content.text: Purchaser shall deliver to First American Title Insurance Company (“Escrow Agent”), within three (3) business days after the Effective Date, an earnest money deposit (the “Initial Deposit”) in the amount of One Hundred Sixty-Two Thousand Five Hundred and 00/100 Dollars ($162,500.00).  In the event that Purchaser delivers the Closing Notice (as defined below) to Seller, then within three (3) business days following the expiration of the Approval Period (as defined below), Purchaser shall make an additional deposit (the “Additional Deposit”, and together with the Initial Deposit, the “Earnest Money”) with Escrow Agent in the amount of One Hundred Sixty-Two Thousand Five Hundred and 00/100 Dollars ($162,500.00).
content.caption: Purchaser shall deliver to First American Title Insurance Co...

content.text: The Initial Deposit and the Additional Deposit, if made, shall be invested by the Escrow Agent in an FDIC-insured, interest-bearing account as Purchaser shall direct; provided, however, that the Earnest Money shall not be placed in any account which would in any way delay the ability of the Escrow Agent to immediately release the Earnest Money under the conditions and terms contained in this Agreement.  If the sale of the Property is consummated under this Agreement, the Earnest Money shall be paid to Seller and applied as a credit against the Purchase Price at Closing.  If Purchaser terminates (or is deemed to have terminated) this Agreement in accordance with any right to terminate granted to Purchaser by the terms of this Agreement, the Earnest Money shall be immediately returned to Purchaser by the Escrow Agent, without the consent or joinder of Seller being required, and neither party hereto shall have any further rights or obligations under this Agreement except for such obligations which by their terms expressly survive the termination of this Agreement (the “Surviving Obligations”).
content.caption: The Initial Deposit and the Additional Deposit, if made, shall be invested by the Escrow Agent in an FDIC-insured, interest-bearing account as Purchaser shall direct; provided, however, that the Earnest Money shall not be placed in any account which would in any way delay the ability of the Escrow Agent to immediately release the Earnest Money under the conditions and terms contained in this Agreement.

content.text: DUE DILIGENCE; TITLE
content.caption: DUE DILIGENCE; TITLE

content.text: Seller’s Obligations.  Seller shall deliver to Purchaser (at Seller’s expense) true, correct, complete and legible copies of all of the due diligence items listed on Schedule A attached hereto and incorporated herein with respect to the Property (collectively, the “Due Diligence Items”) within Seller’s possession or control.  Notwithstanding the foregoing or anything to the contrary contained in this Agreement, Purchaser may request additional information, documentation or materials concerning the Property from Seller at any time after the Effective Date, and Seller agrees to use commercially reasonable efforts to provide such additional information, documentation or materials to Purchaser, provided it is within Seller’s possession or control, and further provided that the delivery or non-delivery of any such additional item shall in no manner extend the Approval Period.
content.caption: Seller’s Obligations.

content.text: Approval Period.  During the period commencing on the Effective Date and expiring at 5:00 p.m. Pacific Time on March 5, 2026 (the “Approval Period”), Purchaser may terminate this Agreement by delivering written notice of such termination to Seller at any time prior to the expiration of the Approval Period, if, in Purchaser’s sole and absolute discretion, Purchaser decides not to consummate the purchase of the Property contemplated hereby for any reason whatsoever, including without limitation, if Purchaser determines that the Property is not suitable for Purchaser’s intended use or it is not satisfied with any items of its due diligence.  In such event, this Agreement will terminate as of the date of such notice, the Escrow Agent shall immediately return all of the Earnest Money to Purchaser, without the consent or joinder of Seller being required, and neither party shall have any further rights or obligations hereunder except for the Surviving Obligations.  If, in Purchaser’s sole and absolute discretion, Purchaser determines that it desires to consummate the purchase of the Property contemplated hereby, then Purchaser will give written notice thereof (the “Closing Notice”) to Seller, prior to the expiration of the Approval Period.  In the event that Purchaser provides Seller with the Closing Notice, then Purchaser will be deemed to have waived its termination rights under this Section 3.2, and the parties will proceed to Closing, subject to all other terms and conditions of this Agreement.  If Purchaser does not give Seller the Closing Notice prior to the expiration of the Approval Period and has not previously terminated this Agreement by written notice to Seller, then this Agreement automatically shall terminate upon the expiration of the Approval Period, and, in such event, the Escrow Agent shall immediately return all of the Earnest Money to Purchaser, without the consent or joinder of Seller being required, and neither party shall have any further rights or obligations hereunder except for the Surviving Obligations.  Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Agreement, Closing Notices and notices to terminate this Agreement prior to the expiration of the Approval Period may be given, by Purchaser as provided in this Agreement or by Purchaser’s attorney by email to Seller and Seller’s attorney.
content.caption: Approval Period.

content.text: Title Commitment.
content.caption: Title Commitment.

content.text: Seller shall convey fee simple title to the Property to Purchaser at Closing, subject only to the Permitted Encumbrances (defined below).  Within five (5) business days following the Effective Date, Purchaser shall obtain, at its sole cost and expense, and deliver to Seller, a title commitment (the “Title Commitment”) for a standard form ALTA Owner’s Policy of Title Insurance (the “Title Policy”) in the amount of the Purchase Price, issued by First American Title Insurance Company (the “Title Company”), insuring good and marketable fee simple title to the Property, together with legible copies of all exceptions listed therein.  Purchaser shall have ten (10) business days following its receipt of the Title Commitment, legible copies of all exceptions listed therein and the Survey (defined below), to deliver to Seller written notice (the “Title Objection Letter”) of Purchaser’s objections to title (the “Title Objections”).
content.caption: Seller shall convey fee simple title to the Property to Purchaser at Closing, subject only to the Permitted Encumbrances (defined below).

content.text: Seller shall have the right, but not the obligation, to use reasonable efforts to cause the Title Company to remove or, with Purchaser’s approval (not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed), affirmatively insure over the Title Objections as an exception to the Purchaser’s Owner’s Title Policy, without any additional cost or liability to the Purchaser (“Remove”); subject, however, to Seller’s obligation to remove all Mandatory Removal Exceptions (as defined below) by Closing.  Seller shall notify Purchaser in writing within five (5) days following Seller’s receipt of the Title Objection Letter concerning which Title Objections, if any, Seller has agreed to Remove.
content.caption: Seller shall have the right, but not the obligation, to use reasonable efforts to cause the Title Company to remove or, with Purchaser’s approval (not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed), affirmatively insure over the Title Objections as an exception to the Purchaser’s Owner’s Title Policy, without any additional cost or liability to the Purchaser (“Remove”); subject, however, to Seller’s obligation to remove all Mandatory Removal Exceptions (as defined below) by Closing.

content.text: In the event that Seller does not undertake to Remove all of the Title Objections in the Title Objection Letter to Purchaser’s sole satisfaction (or does not timely respond to the Title Objection Letter), then Seller shall be deemed to have elected not to Remove any Title Objections not specifically agreed to by Seller and Purchaser shall have the right for five (5) days after receipt of Seller’s response to the Title Objection Letter (or five (5) days following the expiration of the period within which Seller was to so respond) to either (i) waive any such Title Objection in writing and proceed to Closing (in which event such waived Title Objection shall be deemed to be a “Permitted Encumbrance”, as defined below), or (ii)  terminate this Agreement upon written notice to Seller and receive an immediate refund of the Earnest Money, without the consent or joinder of Seller being required, in which event neither party hereto shall have any further rights or obligations under this Agreement except for the Surviving Obligations.  If Seller elects to use reasonable efforts to Remove any one or more Title Objections, Seller shall use such efforts to Remove such Purchaser Title Objections on or before the Closing Date, except that (y) Seller shall in no event be required to bring suit to clear any claimed title or survey defects and (z) except for Mandatory Removal Exceptions, Seller shall not be required to expend more than a total of Fifty Thousand Dollars ($50,000) in the aggregate to Remove the Title Objections.

content.text: All exceptions set forth in the Title Commitment or on the Survey which are not objected to by Purchaser (including matters initially objected to by Purchaser which objections are subsequently waived in writing, and including such standard pre-printed exceptions as are customarily contained in an ALTA owner’s policy (to the extent not removed by the Title Company upon delivery of customary affidavits and indemnities without cost or liability to Purchaser)) are herein collectively called the “Permitted Encumbrances”.  In the event that any update to the Title Commitment or Survey indicates the existence of any Encumbrances or other defects or exceptions which were not shown in the initial Title Commitment or Survey and that are unacceptable to Purchaser (the “Intervening Objections”), in its sole discretion, Purchaser shall, within five (5) business days after receipt of any such update to the Title Commitment or Survey, notify Seller in writing of its objection to any such unacceptable Intervening Objections (the “Intervening Objection Notice”).  Subject to Seller’s obligation to remove all Mandatory Removal Exceptions, Seller shall have no obligation to take any steps or bring any action or proceeding or otherwise to incur any expense whatsoever to eliminate or modify any of the Intervening Objections.  In the event Seller is unable, unwilling or for any reason fails to eliminate or modify all of the Unacceptable Encumbrances to the sole satisfaction of Purchaser, Purchaser may terminate this Agreement by delivering notice thereof in writing to Seller by the earliest to occur of (i) three (3) days after Seller’s written notice to Purchaser of Seller’s intent to not Remove one or more of such unacceptable Intervening Encumbrances, or (ii) five (5) days after the Intervening Objection Notice, in the event Seller does not timely respond thereto.  Upon a termination of this Agreement pursuant to the immediately preceding sentence, the Earnest Money shall be immediately returned to Purchaser, without the consent or joinder of Seller being required, and neither party shall have any further rights or obligations hereunder other than the Surviving Obligations; provided, however, if Seller has committed to Remove any Intervening Objection, then Seller’s subsequent failure to remove such Intervening Objection shall constitute a failed closing condition.  If Seller elects to use reasonable efforts to Remove any one or more Intervening Encumbrances objected to by Purchaser, Seller shall use such efforts to Remove such Intervening Encumbrance(s) on or before the Closing Date, except that (y) Seller shall in no event be required to bring suit to clear any claimed title or	 survey defects and (z) except for Mandatory Removal Exceptions, Seller shall not be required to expend more than a total of Fifty Thousand Dollars ($50,000) in the aggregate to Remove the Intervening Objection together with the initial Title Objections.

content.text: Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained herein, Seller shall, prior to Closing and without any requirement that Purchaser further object thereto, eliminate by paying or otherwise discharging in a manner satisfactory to Purchaser (i) any mortgages, deeds of trust, deeds to secure debt, mechanics’ or materialman’s liens, income tax liens, delinquent property tax liens, or other similar liens securing monetary obligations or monetary judgments created by or through Seller that appear on the Title Commitment, (ii) any and all judgment liens against Seller, and (iii) any exception or Encumbrance created by, under or through Seller after the Effective Date (collectively, “Mandatory Removal Exceptions”). content.text: Survey.  Purchaser may obtain, at its sole cost and expense, a current, as-built ALTA survey of the Property prepared by a registered surveyor acceptable to Purchaser (the “Survey”), which may be an update of the existing survey delivered by Seller to Purchaser pursuant to Section 3.1 above.  If Purchaser elects to obtain a Survey, it shall order the Survey within five (5) days after the Effective Date.  If Purchaser fails to timely order the Survey, Purchaser’s right to object to matters appearing on any future survey shall be deemed waived.  The Survey (and all related survey certifications) shall be addressed to both Purchaser and Seller.  Purchaser shall deliver a .pdf of any final Survey to Seller promptly upon receipt thereof by Purchaser.
content.caption: Survey.

content.text: Contracts.  Purchaser shall notify Seller prior to the expiration of the Approval Period which of the Contracts Purchaser will require Seller to cancel at Closing (the “Rejected Contracts”), and Seller hereby agrees to cancel same not later than Closing, at Seller’s sole cost and expense.  All Contracts which Purchaser does not designate as Rejected Contracts by the end of the Approval Period, and any other Contracts that cannot be terminated without cause by Seller and without payment of any fee or penalty by Seller, shall be deemed approved by Purchaser and shall be assigned to and assumed by Purchaser at the Closing pursuant to the Assignment and Assumption Agreement.  Additionally, any Contracts which are not assignable shall be the sole responsibility of Seller, shall be cancelled by Seller on or before Closing.
content.caption: Contracts.

content.text: Inspection.  During the Approval Period and, if Purchaser delivers a Closing Notice through Closing, at any time and from time to time during normal business hours, Purchaser may inspect, test, and survey, in accordance with that certain Access and Confidentiality Agreement, dated January 19, 2026, between Seller and Purchaser (“Access Agreement”): (a) the Property and any and all portions thereof, including physical and mechanical inspections, (b) the Due Diligence Items, and (c) originals of all Leases, Tower Leases, Billboard Leases, and Contracts. Seller shall cooperate in good faith (at no cost to Seller) with Purchaser, Purchaser’s agents and independent contractors in connection with all such inspections, tests and surveys, including, without limitation, obtaining all necessary tenant consents and/or providing adequate notice to tenants regarding Purchaser’s entry into leased areas on the Property, making reasonably available during normal business hours all relevant personnel to answer any questions which Purchaser may have regarding the Property, and providing such documents and materials in its possession or control (and which do not constitute Excluded Items) reasonably requested from time to time by Purchaser in connection with Purchaser’s due diligence efforts.
content.caption: Inspection.

content.text: Reporting.  In the event that Purchaser’s due diligence reveals any condition of the Property that in Purchaser’s judgment requires disclosure to any governmental agency or authority, Purchaser shall immediately notify Seller thereof.  In such event, Seller, and not Purchaser or anyone acting on Purchaser’s behalf, shall make such disclosures as Seller deems appropriate.  Notwithstanding the foregoing, Purchaser may disclose matters concerning the Property to a governmental authority if, (a) in the written opinion of Purchaser’s outside legal counsel, Purchaser is required by law to make such disclosure, and (b) Purchaser gives Seller not less than ten (10) days prior written notice of the proposed disclosure, together with a copy of such legal opinion

content.text: Seller Holdback.  At the Closing, Seller shall deposit the sum of $[___________] (the “Escrow Proceeds”) into escrow with the Title Company, pursuant to an escrow agreement in form attached hereto as Exhibit I and incorporated herein, to provide a source of recovery for any post-closing claims that Purchaser may have against Seller either under this Agreement or under the documents executed by Seller at Closing.  To the extent a claim is made by Purchaser against Seller following Closing, Purchaser shall be entitled to a disbursement of a portion of the Escrow Proceeds equal to the amount of such claim, without limitation of Purchaser’s right to recover the entire amount of any claim against Seller should the then balance of the Escrow Proceeds be insufficient.  The Escrow Proceeds shall be held in escrow until the first anniversary of the Closing Date, at which time any undisbursed Escrow Proceeds shall be released to Seller; provided, however, that in the event a claim is then pending against Seller by Purchaser, there shall be withheld from such disbursement an amount equal to the amount of such claim; provided further, however, that in the event that such pending claim exceeds the then balance of the Escrow Proceeds then there shall be no disbursement to Seller at such time.
content.caption: Seller Holdback.

Escrow Agent further agrees that it will not pay or attempt to pay or otherwise satisfy any claims it may have against Seller or Purchaser, whether arising under this Agreement or otherwise, from the Escrow Deposit.

content.text:
ARTICLE II
DISTRIBUTION OF THE ESCROW DEPOSIT
content.caption: DISTRIBUTION OF THE ESCROW DEPOSIT

content.text: 2.01	Purchaser’s Withdrawal.  Subject to the terms of this Section 2.01, Purchaser shall be entitled to withdraw funds from the Escrow Deposit five (5) business days following delivery of a certificate (a “Withdrawal Certificate”) to Escrow Agent, executed by Purchaser, indicating (a) that Purchaser has a claim (and describing such claim in reasonable detail) against Seller as a result of a Seller Liability, and (b) as a result of such claim, Purchaser is owed money by Seller.  All Withdrawal Certificates shall include a statement of the fixed amount to which Purchaser is entitled as a result of its claim and the amount to be paid to Purchaser from the Escrow Deposit.  All Withdrawal Certificates shall be delivered simultaneously to Seller and the Escrow Agent in accordance with Section 4.01 of this Agreement.  Notwithstanding anything to the contrary set forth in this Section 2.01 or elsewhere in this Agreement, in no event shall Escrow Agent make any disbursements under this Agreement with respect to any Withdrawal Certificate that is being disputed by Seller (other than interpleading such funds), as evidenced by written notice regarding such dispute provided by Seller to Escrow Agent and Purchaser within five (5) business days following Purchaser’s delivery of a Withdrawal Certificate.
content.caption: Purchaser’s Withdrawal.

content.text: 2.02	Termination and Return of Escrow Deposit.  On the date that is three hundred sixty five (365) days after the date of this Agreement (the “Termination Date”), if Purchaser has not delivered a Withdrawal Certificate which remains unpaid, Seller shall have the right to instruct Escrow Agent to return to Seller the Escrow Deposit (or the remaining portion of the Escrow Deposit, if any disbursements of the Escrow Deposit have been made hereunder), whereupon the Escrow Agent shall disburse such sums to Seller.  On the Termination Date, if Purchaser has delivered a Withdrawal Certificate, and such Withdrawal Certificate remains unpaid, then the portion of the Escrow Deposit equal to the amount of such claim (or the then balance of the Escrow Deposit if lesser than the amount of such claim) shall remain on deposit with the Escrow Agent until the final resolution of such claim; provided, however, that in the event the amount claimed by Purchaser with respect to such Seller Liability is less than the amount of the Escrow Deposit at such time, then Seller shall have the right to instruct the Escrow Agent to return any excess portion of the Escrow Deposit to Seller.
content.caption: Termination and Return of Escrow Deposit.

section_hierarchy.caption: Termination and Return of Escrow Deposit.

content.text: 2.03	Timing of Disbursements.  Escrow Agent shall make disbursements from the Escrow Deposit not earlier than five (5) business days following receipt of a Withdrawal Certificate or other written instructions directing the Escrow Agent to disburse funds in accordance with this Agreement.  Unless otherwise agreed by Escrow Agent and the recipient of funds from the Escrow Deposit, disbursements shall be made by the Escrow Agent’s check, delivered to Seller or Purchaser, as appropriate, at their respective addresses for notice under this Agreement.
content.caption: Timing of Disbursements.

content.text: 2.04	Cooperation.  Seller and Purchaser agree to cooperate with each other and with Escrow Agent to facilitate the disbursements and withdrawals contemplated by this Agreement.  Accordingly, upon request of Escrow Agent, Seller and Purchaser shall each execute such additional instructions and directions as may reasonably be requested by Escrow Agent consistent with the terms of this Agreement; provided, however, that such additional instructions shall not be a condition to any withdrawal of the Escrow Deposit unless otherwise provided herein.
content.caption: Cooperation.

content.text: 2.05	Termination of Agreement.  This Agreement shall terminate, without any further action on the part of Seller, Purchaser or Escrow Agent, upon disbursement in full of the Escrow Deposit in accordance with this Agreement.
content.caption: Termination of Agreement.

content.text:
ARTICLE III
ESCROW AGENT
content.caption: ESCROW AGENT

content.text: 3.01	Acceptance of Agreement.  Escrow Agent, by reason of its consent to and execution of this Agreement, for the fees to be paid hereunder, hereby agrees to act as escrow agent for the Escrow Deposit in accordance with this Agreement and to be bound by this Agreement in the performance of its duties hereunder.  Escrow Agent shall not, however, assume any responsibility or liability for any transaction between Seller and Purchaser other than for the performance of its obligations with respect to the Escrow Deposit in accordance with this Agreement.  The duties and responsibilities of Escrow Agent shall be limited to those expressly set forth herein.
content.caption: Acceptance of Agreement.

content.text: 3.02	Limited Responsibilities.  Escrow Agent shall be under no responsibility in respect of the Escrow Deposit other than faithfully to follow the instructions contained herein.  Escrow Agent may consult with counsel of its own choosing and shall be fully protected in any action taken in good faith, in accordance with such consultation.  Escrow Agent shall not be required to defend any legal proceedings that may be instituted unless requested so to do by Seller and Purchaser, and shall be indemnified by Seller and Purchaser, jointly and severally, to its satisfaction against the cost and expense of such defense.  Escrow Agent shall have no responsibility for the genuineness or validity of any document or other item deposited with Escrow Agent and it shall be fully protected in acting in accordance with written instructions to it hereunder and believed by Escrow Agent to have been signed by the proper parties.  Escrow Agent is not required to be familiar with the provisions of any other instrument or agreement and shall not be charged with any responsibility or liability in connection with the observance or nonobservance by any person having duties or obligations under any such instrument or agreement.
content.caption: Limited Responsibilities.

content.text: 3.03	Indemnification.  Except for claims, liabilities, judgments, or expenses incurred by the parties due to a negligent act, error or omission of Escrow Agent in the performance of its obligations hereunder, and except for fees and expenses for which Seller and Purchaser are exclusively responsible pursuant to Section 1.03 hereof, Seller and Purchaser shall jointly and severally indemnify, protect and save Escrow Agent harmless from any claims, liabilities, judgments, reasonable attorneys’ fees, and other expenses of any kind and nature that may be incurred by Escrow Agent by reason of its acceptance of, and its good faith performance under, this Agreement.
content.caption: Indemnification.

content.text: 3.04	Compliance with Order of Court.  Escrow Agent is hereby expressly instructed by Seller and Purchaser to comply with and obey all orders, judgments or decrees of any court with jurisdiction and in case Escrow Agent complies with any such order, judgment or decree, Escrow Agent shall not be liable to Seller or Purchaser or to any other person or entity by reason of compliance.  In complying with the foregoing, if Escrow Agent becomes or is made a party to any court proceeding which affects this Agreement, Escrow Agent shall promptly give notice thereof to Seller and Purchaser.  To the extent possible in any such proceeding, Escrow Agent shall interplead the Escrow Deposit.  If Escrow Agent receives any such order from any court, to the extent possible and consistent with the language of such order, Escrow Agent shall delay compliance until Seller and Purchaser have had an opportunity to advise Escrow Agent of the respective position of each of Seller and Purchaser with regard to compliance.
content.caption: Compliance with Order of Court.

content.text: 3.05	Disputes.  If a dispute arises as to the duties of any party under the terms of this Agreement, Escrow Agent may file suit in interpleader for the purpose of having the respective rights of Escrow Agent, Seller and Purchaser adjudicated.  Upon filing its complaint in interpleader, Escrow Agent shall be relieved from all further liability under the provisions of this Agreement.
content.caption: Disputes.
